### 3.6.2 Create `Board` Class

The board holds an array of squares and can return a square by position.

```java
package knowledgequest;

public class Board {
    private BoardSquare[] squares;

    public Board(int size) {
        squares = new BoardSquare[size];
        // Initialize squares
        for (int i = 0; i < size; i++) {
            String type = "normal";
            String desc = "Just a square";
            if (i % 5 == 0) {
                type = "question";
                desc = "Answer a question!";
            } else if (i % 7 == 0) {
                type = "bonus";
                desc = "Bonus points!";
            } else if (i % 11 == 0) {
                type = "penalty";
                desc = "Oops! Lose points!";
            }
            squares[i] = new BoardSquare(i, type, desc);
        }
    }

    public BoardSquare getSquare(int position) {
        if (position >= 0 && position < squares.length) {
            return squares[position];
        }
        return null;
    }

    public int getSize() {
        return squares.length;
    }
}
```

